00:11:54,420 --> 00:11:56,220
[You think it's only about speed?]

253
00:11:56,300 --> 00:11:58,780
[This is the key point!]

254
00:11:59,340 --> 00:12:01,580
[The conehead conquering all resistance!]

255
00:12:01,740 --> 00:12:05,060
[Here comes a tornado!]

256
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:08,820
[An alien going all out!]

257
00:12:09,860 --> 00:12:13,180
[Stunned]

258
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:13,480
NuNew: Wow!

259
00:12:15,260 --> 00:12:18,580
[Phuak, whose speed matches his skill]

260
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:23,420
[Knocked down a lot of bowling pins]

261
00:12:23,540 --> 00:12:25,100
Offroad: Wow, that's so many!

262
00:12:23,540 --> 00:12:25,100
[The bar's already sky-high from the start]

263
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:26,300
Ink: Wow, so many.

264
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:27,540
NuNew: Ah, so many.

265
00:12:27,540 --> 00:12:29,900
[Dissatisfied with Phuak's strategy]

266
00:12:27,820 --> 00:12:30,280
Ink: His legs were like this, like this.

267
00:12:30,280 --> 00:12:31,660
Phuak: No, no, it was...

268
00:12:32,020 --> 00:12:33,020
Phuak: it was caused by that momentum.

269
00:12:33,020 --> 00:12:35,380
[Everything stems
from the laws of physics]

270
00:12:33,290 --> 00:12:35,640
Phuak: It's momentum,
the power of momentum.

271
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:37,900
Jeff: Your head got dented from rolling.

272
00:12:38,660 --> 00:12:39,460
Jeff: Your head is dented in.

273
00:12:39,460 --> 00:12:42,020
Phuak: I rolled and rolled. I got dizzy.

274
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:48,140
[Although the head is dented,
the score is good]

275
00:12:44,940 --> 00:12:45,800
Phuak: Well...

276
00:12:49,540 --> 00:12:52,740
[The second person, Hellboy Jeff]

277
00:12:57,900 --> 00:13:02,220
[Time to move the body]

278
00:13:03,420 --> 00:13:06,100
[Need to knock down the pins, right?]

279
00:13:06,980 --> 00:13:10,500
[Watch me smash them in half…]

280
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:14,180
[Jeff already looks like
a winner just walking in]

281
00:13:11,220 --> 00:13:14,300
Ink: So Jeff's just got the win
all figured out?

282
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:16,480
Tay: Jeff, can you not be so serious?

283
00:13:18,260 --> 00:13:21,780
[I'm not here to play around]

284
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:24,420
[Hellboy Jeff, get ready!]

285
00:13:28,980 --> 00:13:30,900
[His speed is no joke]

286
00:13:32,060 --> 00:13:33,660
NuNew: Wow, that's intense!

287
00:13:33,940 --> 00:13:35,300
Phuak: Oh my, oh my.

288
00:13:36,300 --> 00:13:39,340
[That looks like he's about
to crush the pins]

289
00:13:39,480 --> 00:13:41,420
[Rushing towards the pins]

290
00:13:42,260 --> 00:13:44,960
[?]

291
00:13:45,020 --> 00:13:48,340
[What happened to Hellboy Jeff?]

292
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:47,580
Phuak: Oh, huh?

293
00:13:48,620 --> 00:13:50,100
[While he was sliding fast,]

294
00:13:50,180 --> 00:13:53,500
[he suddenly lost balance
and flipped over!]

295
00:13:57,420 --> 00:14:00,740
[Completely throwing off his direction]

296
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:04,300
Phuak: Very few, very few.

297
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:06,100
Phuak: Oh, maybe...

298
00:14:04,860 --> 00:14:07,940
[Could this be the first time
beating Jeff?]

299
00:14:06,100 --> 00:14:08,220
-Offroad: Maybe you...
-Phuak: Maybe I...

300
00:14:08,220 --> 00:14:11,300
[Human games are harder than I thought]

301
00:14:12,860 --> 00:14:15,940
[What a pity]

302
00:14:16,980 --> 00:14:19,660
[It's Meowerine NuNew's turn]

303
00:14:18,640 --> 00:14:20,530
NuNew: Wow, in here...

304
00:14:19,740 --> 00:14:22,300
[Checking and getting ready]

305
00:14:22,420 --> 00:14:25,260
[A good start is half the win]

306
00:14:22,660 --> 00:14:25,220
NuNew: What a great start to the day

307
00:14:26,340 --> 00:14:28,800
[Turning as planned]

308
00:14:29,740 --> 00:14:32,820
[Meowerine spin strategy]

309
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:34,620
Phuak: Wow, he keeps spinning.

310
00:14:33,260 --> 00:14:36,340
[What a cheerful alien]

311
00:14:35,300 --> 00:14:36,780
Ink: He'll be dizzy in a moment.

312
00:14:36,780 --> 00:14:41,500
[Getting ready to go, all excited]

313
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:41,060
PD: Start once you hear the whistle.

314
00:14:41,060 --> 00:14:41,790
NuNew: Okay.

315
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:44,260
NuNew: Oh, I'm scared.

316
00:14:43,540 --> 00:14:45,300
[Turned out to be scared just
as he was about to start...]

317
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:48,820
[Eventually gathered the courage
to rush out]

318
00:14:49,260 --> 00:14:49,900
[Aiya!]

319
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:54,420
-Phuak: Wow.
-Jeff: He even made an "aiya" sound.

320
00:14:52,820 --> 00:14:55,380
[Meowerine's followers
are watching from the sidelines]

321
00:14:54,420 --> 00:14:56,550
Phuak: Why did he make an "aiya" sound?

322
00:14:59,940 --> 00:15:04,020
[This is the Meowerine's trait—
when he locks onto something]

323
00:15:04,260 --> 00:15:07,580
[like pouncing on a cat treat!]

324
00:15:07,660 --> 00:15:10,980
[I'm going to eat them all!]

325
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:10,920
NuNew: Ah, go!

326
00:15:14,660 --> 00:15:18,100
[He even spun at the end,
just like he's practiced it before]

327
00:15:19,380 --> 00:15:20,940
Ink: He even did a spin.

328
00:15:20,940 --> 00:15:24,380
[Our little kitty is giving it his all
to knock down the pins]

329
00:15:22,140 --> 00:15:24,070
NuNew: My body just spun on its own.

330
00:15:25,460 --> 00:15:28,900
[Next is Tay,
the ape-man from outer space]

331
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:35,700
[?]

332
00:15:35,780 --> 00:15:38,120
[Back up] [Back up]

333
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:42,620
Tay: Can I charge up my energy?

334
00:15:42,660 --> 00:15:46,100
[Starting far back to build momentum]

335
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:43,830
Tay: Charging up...

336
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:49,160
-Phuak: Wow, he's going way too far
-Ink: Ah, this is too far.

337
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:53,360
Phuak: Go ahead and charge up.
You can go to the edge of the forest over there.

338
00:15:53,540 --> 00:15:56,760
[Backing up, backing up...]
[Let me step back a few more]

339
00:15:56,820 --> 00:15:58,880
[Is he backing all the way to Bangkok?]

340
00:15:58,880 --> 00:16:01,540
[Ape-man Tay]
[Finally ready!]

341
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:05,500
[Those pins are going down!]

342
00:16:05,660 --> 00:16:09,100
[That's pretty far from the launch point]

343
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:18,540
[Full acceleration]

344
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:20,200
[Looks like Tay is doing pretty well]

345
00:16:20,510 --> 00:16:22,790
[2 young men yet to go
are observing the situation closely]

346
00:16:24,890 --> 00:16:26,330
[A precise hit right in the center]

347
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:31,100
[Put in all that effort to run so far,
only to get a score similar to NuNew's!]

348
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:29,730
Ink: Wow!

349
00:16:29,730 --> 00:16:30,720
Jeff: About the same as NuNew.

350
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:32,150
Phuak: Neck and neck, almost the same.

351
00:16:32,150 --> 00:16:34,240
Ink: What's wrong? Are you "dead?"

352
00:16:35,300 --> 00:16:38,420
[He's completely out of energy,
can't even stand]

353
00:16:35,740 --> 00:16:37,140
Ink: Hey, get up quickly!

354
00:16:37,690 --> 00:16:38,340
Phuak: You can't get up?

355
00:16:38,340 --> 00:16:39,790
-Ink: Tay, get up.
-Phuak: Tay, get up quickly.

356
00:16:39,790 --> 00:16:41,040
Ink: Get up quickly!

357
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:42,560
Phuak: He can't get up.

358
00:16:42,750 --> 00:16:46,010
[Struggling] [Crawling]

359
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:49,150
-Ink: Look at Tay.
-Jeff: Oh, he can't get up.

360
00:16:49,150 --> 00:16:50,970
Ink: Look at Tay.

361
00:16:51,560 --> 00:16:54,680
[This man is completely drained]

362
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:59,070
NuNew: He can't even lift his legs.
They're just dragging along.

363
00:16:56,400 --> 00:16:59,000
[Next is Offroad—a boy from the Naga tribe,
a Na'vi hybrid descendant]

364
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:04,220
Ink: Well, will heavier people
slide faster?

365
00:16:59,390 --> 00:17:02,360
[Will heavier people go faster?]

366
00:17:04,220 --> 00:17:05,359
-Offroad: No.
-Ink: Really?

367
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:09,880
Offroad: Right, you have to be light.
I think the key lies in the initial velocity.

368
00:17:09,880 --> 00:17:11,710
Ink: Ooh, Offroad is already calculating.

369
00:17:11,710 --> 00:17:14,940
Offroad: Only by reaching that initial velocity
can impact force be generated.

370
00:17:14,940 --> 00:17:17,869
Offroad: S = v₀t + (1/2)at²

371
00:17:17,869 --> 00:17:19,220
Ink: Fine, just let him be.

372
00:17:19,220 --> 00:17:22,150
[Theoretical knowledge is maxed out]

373
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:25,440
Offroad: Ouch, it's caught on my ear,
caught on my ear.

374
00:17:27,050 --> 00:17:28,520
[Preparing to slide]

375
00:17:28,590 --> 00:17:31,090
[Backing up to find a good starting point]

376
00:17:31,930 --> 00:17:33,730
[Increasing distance to create speed]

377
00:17:34,180 --> 00:17:35,020
Tay: He's for real.

378
00:17:34,540 --> 00:17:37,220
[This kid looks very serious]

379
00:17:35,020 --> 00:17:37,710
Ink: Offroad was really calculating.
He was already doing math in his head just now.

380
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:39,270
[If he does it as calculated...
he'll hit every single one]

381
00:17:39,900 --> 00:17:41,240
Offroad: Can I start?

382
00:17:40,140 --> 00:17:41,840
[Ready!]

383
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,390
[Let's see what you've got]

384
00:17:47,550 --> 00:17:50,550
Offroad: I think the key lies
in the initial velocity.

385
00:17:47,550 --> 00:17:49,800
[I think the key lies in initial velocity]

386
00:17:53,010 --> 00:17:54,370
[The speed looks OK]

387
00:17:55,390 --> 00:17:56,690
[But...]

388
00:17:57,730 --> 00:17:59,680
[It actually veered straight
to the right?]

389
00:18:02,430 --> 00:18:03,800
[Spinning]

390
00:18:06,410 --> 00:18:09,750
[Offroad swept the pins down
by spinning]

391
00:18:10,350 --> 00:18:14,480
[A nice turnaround of the situation!]

392
00:18:16,320 --> 00:18:19,970
[The Naga tribe's spinning power
has come into play]

393
00:18:20,570 --> 00:18:22,060
Phuak: He can even do a side spin?

394
00:18:22,060 --> 00:18:22,760
Ink: He spins just like...

395
00:18:22,760 --> 00:18:25,050
Phuak: It has a bit of a curve.

396
00:18:25,290 --> 00:18:26,990
NuNew: You spun like a drill.

397
00:18:27,510 --> 00:18:29,510
Offroad: I couldn't control it.

398
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:31,540
Phuak: Oh, you lost control.

399
00:18:31,760 --> 00:18:32,490
-Offroad: Yes, Phuak.
- Yes, Phuak.

400
00:18:32,490 --> 00:18:34,910
Phuak: So it just kept spinning,
like it rolled over.

401
00:18:34,910 --> 00:18:36,170
Offroad: Oh, Phuak, it's so hard.

402
00:18:36,170 --> 00:18:39,200
[Calculations were fine,
but ruined by the lack of stability]

403
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:40,610
Ink: Yeah, it's really hard.

404
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:41,870
[The next is Ink—
a hybrid of mantis and alien]

405
00:18:40,750 --> 00:18:42,100
-Phuak: Great.
-NuNew: I'm afraid of losing.

406
00:18:42,100 --> 00:18:45,630
[Human games are truly strange]

407
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:50,170
[Firing off questions nonstop]

408
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:47,210
Ink: I have to slide over?

409
00:18:47,300 --> 00:18:48,750
Ink: Does it hurt, or is it just scary?

410
00:18:48,750 --> 00:18:50,430
Ink: Is it tiring running that far?

411
00:18:50,430 --> 00:18:51,670
Ink: Ah, the pressure is so high!

412
00:18:50,430 --> 00:18:51,670
[So much pressure!]

413
00:18:52,310 --> 00:18:55,160
[Ever since arriving on Earth,
the pressure hasn't stopped]

414
00:18:53,410 --> 00:18:54,810
Ink: I'm so stressed out.

415
00:18:56,250 --> 00:18:57,290
Ink: Okay.

416
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:59,040
[Despite the smile on the face...]

417
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:00,860
Ink: Ah, so much pressure.

418
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:00,370
[Wuwu, so much pressure]

419
00:19:01,130 --> 00:19:02,610
[Let's end this game quickly!]

420
00:19:01,360 --> 00:19:02,490
Ink: I'll get ready.

421
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:04,660
[I'm going to sweep them all away!]

422
00:19:11,770 --> 00:19:14,120
[Staring intensely at the bowling pins]

423
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:16,190
[The start looks okay, but...]

424
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:15,410
Phuak: Hey, hey, not there yet.

425
00:19:15,410 --> 00:19:16,210
Tay: Hurry up.

426
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:17,370
Phuak: Hey, hey, not there yet.

427
00:19:17,370 --> 00:19:18,740
Tay: Hurry, Ink!

428
00:19:18,810 --> 00:19:20,670
Phuak: Ink, Ink.

429
00:19:23,740 --> 00:19:26,720
-Tay: Hurry, Ink!
-Phuak: Ink!

430
00:19:28,050 --> 00:19:29,700
[Humph]

431
00:19:30,020 --> 00:19:32,140
[Ended up sliding only halfway]

432
00:19:33,020 --> 00:19:36,360
[Causing the alien companions
to feel the pressure, too]

433
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:35,020
Phuak: A bit further, a bit further.

434
00:19:35,020 --> 00:19:36,910
-Phuak: A bit further. Roll over.
-Jeff: You can roll over.

435
00:19:36,910 --> 00:19:40,500
[That distance gap is insane]

436
00:19:36,910 --> 00:19:40,170
-Phuak: A bit further. Roll over.
-Jeff: You can roll over.

437
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:45,590
[Pressure levels are off the charts!]

438
00:19:45,820 --> 00:19:47,660
-Phuak: Wow.
-Jeff: You didn't even reach half the distance!

439
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:49,150
[Didn't even slide halfway]

440
00:19:47,660 --> 00:19:49,150
Phuak: It's not even halfway
down the track.

441
00:19:49,150 --> 00:19:51,160
Ink: Why isn't it moving at all?

442
00:19:49,610 --> 00:19:52,720
[Frustration]

443
00:19:52,720 --> 00:19:54,440
NuNew: It's no problem for the boys.

444
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:57,500
NuNew: For Ink, maybe
her starting force was too small.

445
00:19:57,590 --> 00:20:00,560
[The puppy-like soft alien TeeTee
can't smile at all now]

446
00:20:01,020 --> 00:20:03,100
[Because he is next!]

447
00:20:04,220 --> 00:20:06,830
[Walked to the starting point]

448
00:20:08,470 --> 00:20:10,440
[Body shaking uncontrollably]

449
00:20:08,740 --> 00:20:10,070
TeeTee: I'm so nervous.

450
00:20:11,130 --> 00:20:12,590
TeeTee: Start right away?

451
00:20:13,350 --> 00:20:15,210
TeeTee: Everyone, I'm so nervous.

452
00:20:15,210 --> 00:20:17,350
[Extremely nervous]

453
00:20:16,950 --> 00:20:18,480
TeeTee: My heart is beating so fast.

454
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:20,460
[Trembling all over from fear]

455
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:23,150
[Is it really that scary?]

456
00:20:28,140 --> 00:20:29,710
[Level 1 scream]

457
00:20:28,140 --> 00:20:29,080
[Ah!]

458
00:20:30,460 --> 00:20:31,700
[Level 2 scream]

459
00:20:30,460 --> 00:20:31,350
[Ah!]

460
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:32,960
[Level 3 scream]

461
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:32,730
[Ah!]

462
00:20:33,170 --> 00:20:35,590
[He slid over slowly… with zero impact]

463
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:39,440
[Was the screaming supposed
to boost his damage?]

464
00:20:37,870 --> 00:20:39,440
Phuak: Can he hit them?

465
00:20:39,610 --> 00:20:41,810
[How did it end up like this?]

466
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:41,920
NuNew: Yes.

467
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:45,980
[This speed is completely mismatched
with that soul-wrenching scream]

468
00:20:48,140 --> 00:20:53,640
[Doing his best to imitate
the older bros...]

469
00:20:55,010 --> 00:20:57,500
[Human games are truly terrifying...]

470
00:20:58,060 --> 00:21:00,540
[It's the turn of Por,
the elf from outer space]

471
00:21:03,210 --> 00:21:04,640
[Staring intently]

472
00:21:04,450 --> 00:21:05,850
TeeTee: Good luck, baby.

473
00:21:10,370 --> 00:21:12,560
[Sending full support to his baby]

474
00:21:10,370 --> 00:21:12,280
TeeTee: Hey,
there's a chance this round, bro.

475
00:21:16,270 --> 00:21:17,520
PD: Are you ready?

476
00:21:16,370 --> 00:21:19,360
[Energy bar is full, ready to go!]

477
00:21:17,520 --> 00:21:18,590
Por: Ready.

478
00:21:20,990 --> 00:21:23,920
[Will he be able to show the power of love?]

479
00:21:29,230 --> 00:21:30,540
Tay: Go, go, go.

480
00:21:32,170 --> 00:21:34,240
[Giving it his all for TeeTee, too]

481
00:21:34,670 --> 00:21:37,740
[The posture rushing
towards the pins is beautiful...]

482
00:21:38,740 --> 00:21:42,220
[But he keeps veering
toward the edge of the track]

483
00:21:42,520 --> 00:21:45,850
[His speed dropped,
and he completely lost direction]

484
00:21:46,140 --> 00:21:48,320
[2?]

485
00:21:48,380 --> 00:21:50,590
Phuak: Good, good, good, Por, not bad.

486
00:21:48,470 --> 00:21:50,720
[Wow, only 2…]

487
00:21:50,840 --> 00:21:52,000
TeeTee: It's okay, it's okay.

488
00:21:50,840 --> 00:21:52,000
[It's okay]

489
00:21:52,060 --> 00:21:54,880
[Por, looks like even the power
of love couldn't help]

490
00:21:55,050 --> 00:21:57,320
[Spacecraft, Roll! Roll! Roll! Then Land
mission is complete]

491
00:21:55,580 --> 00:21:58,310
PD: We have successfully
completed the mission.

492
00:21:58,320 --> 00:22:02,700
PD: There is only 1 winner in this game,
and only that person gets a clue.

493
00:22:02,770 --> 00:22:06,740
PD: And the person with the highest score is...

494
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:15,880
[The winner is the conehead alien, Phuak]

495
00:22:12,500 --> 00:22:13,840
PD: Phuak!

496
00:22:14,840 --> 00:22:16,170
Tay: Congratulations.

497
00:22:16,390 --> 00:22:19,460
[Credit also goes to my head!]

498
00:22:19,520 --> 00:22:24,090
[TeeTee: 6, Por: 2]

499
00:22:19,520 --> 00:22:24,090
