00:57:49,130 --> 00:57:49,800
Phuak: Yeah, go ahead.

1751
00:57:49,800 --> 00:57:50,780
[I want to know about the “Humans”]

1752
00:57:49,800 --> 00:57:50,430
NuNew: I want to know
about the Humans.

1753
00:57:50,430 --> 00:57:51,290
Phuak: Humans.

1754
00:57:53,750 --> 00:57:56,010
NuNew: What if there're Humans among us?

1755
00:57:56,060 --> 00:57:58,530
[Yeah…]

1756
00:57:57,280 --> 00:57:58,350
Phuak: Could it be you, NuNew?

1757
00:57:58,350 --> 00:58:00,980
Phuak: But the info on both sides is the same.

1758
00:58:01,000 --> 00:58:01,830
Phuak: Is it the same?

1759
00:58:01,830 --> 00:58:02,340
Phuak: Humans.

1760
00:58:02,000 --> 00:58:05,950
[The 3 choose the clue about “Humans”]

1761
00:58:02,340 --> 00:58:03,200
NuNew: Humans.

1762
00:58:06,300 --> 00:58:10,700
[What kind of clue could it be?]

1763
00:58:11,580 --> 00:58:15,030
[Some Humans have shoe sizes over 40]

1764
00:58:15,360 --> 00:58:16,620
Tay: Everyone, right?

1765
00:58:17,080 --> 00:58:19,500
NuNew: Well, most guys'
shoe sizes are over 40, right?

1766
00:58:19,500 --> 00:58:21,560
Phuak: What's your shoe size, NuNew?

1767
00:58:21,680 --> 00:58:22,610
Tay: NuNew wears size 39, right?

1768
00:58:22,610 --> 00:58:23,400
NuNew: No.

1769
00:58:23,980 --> 00:58:25,000
Phuak: What size do you usually wear?

1770
00:58:25,000 --> 00:58:26,880
Phuak: No, I just want to know if any guys…

1771
00:58:25,350 --> 00:58:29,300
[Are you suspecting me right now?]

1772
00:58:26,880 --> 00:58:27,870
NuNew: Let's exchange.

1773
00:58:27,870 --> 00:58:29,430
Phuak: Are there guys
with feet smaller than that?

1774
00:58:29,430 --> 00:58:30,950
Tay: What about TeeTee and Por?

1775
00:58:30,950 --> 00:58:34,260
Phuak: When those 2 fall asleep,
we'll go measure their feet.

1776
00:58:34,260 --> 00:58:36,680
[That's hilarious]

1777
00:58:34,640 --> 00:58:36,680
NuNew: When are they ever going to sleep?

1778
00:58:36,680 --> 00:58:37,850
Phuak: OK. Let’s go.

1779
00:58:40,080 --> 00:58:41,930
Phuak: Wow, that's a lot of information.

1780
00:58:40,400 --> 00:58:44,530
[Who exactly is the “Human”
with a shoe size over 40?]

1781
00:58:41,930 --> 00:58:42,730
Tay: Yeah, a lot.

1782
00:58:42,730 --> 00:58:44,260
Phuak: That's a lot of info.

1783
00:58:45,830 --> 00:58:51,530
[Final mission of the game
“Return to the Home Planet”]

1784
00:58:49,730 --> 00:58:51,330
Jeff: Watch your step, guys.

1785
00:58:52,700 --> 00:58:55,830
PD: We've reached the final mission—
Name-Tag Ripping.

1786
00:58:58,580 --> 00:59:00,500
Today's  Name-Tag Ripping game

1787
00:59:00,780 --> 00:59:04,580
is a battle between the Spaceship Captain
and the Humans.

1788
00:59:01,700 --> 00:59:04,430
[Match: Spaceship Captain VS Humans]

1789
00:59:08,700 --> 00:59:11,260
PD: In today's  Name-Tag Ripping mission,

1790
00:59:11,600 --> 00:59:18,900
the one who gets
the Spaceship Captain role

1791
00:59:12,160 --> 00:59:23,800
[Rule 1: Aliens & Spaceship Captain
win by eliminating 2 Humans]

1792
00:59:19,330 --> 00:59:23,730
That way, the Spaceship Captain
and the Aliens win.

1793
00:59:24,400 --> 00:59:30,030
Meanwhile, the Humans must find out
who the Spaceship Captain is and eliminate them.

1794
00:59:26,700 --> 00:59:33,680
[Rule 2: Humans win by eliminating all Aliens
or eliminating the Spaceship Captain]

1795
00:59:30,900 --> 00:59:33,760
So they can't return to
their home planet, Planet R.

1796
00:59:34,650 --> 00:59:39,100
Now there are clues about
the Spaceship Captain and the Humans.

1797
00:59:35,500 --> 00:59:44,300
[Rule 3: You must search for
hidden clues around the area]

1798
00:59:39,250 --> 00:59:41,910
They're dispersed and hidden in the buildings.

1799
00:59:44,980 --> 00:59:46,720
Everyone understands the rules, right?

1800
00:59:46,720 --> 00:59:47,400
Yes.

1801
00:59:49,180 --> 00:59:52,350
[In the end, can the Aliens safely escape Earth?]

1802
00:59:53,000 --> 00:59:54,080
Phuak: Let's exchange information.

1803
00:59:54,080 --> 00:59:55,430
Tay: We got the clue together.

1804
00:59:55,430 --> 00:59:56,300
Phuak: Yeah.

1805
01:00:02,930 --> 01:00:04,390
Jeff: Let's go find clues.

1806
01:00:05,530 --> 01:00:06,530
Jeff: Let's go find clues.

1807
01:00:06,530 --> 01:00:11,080
[Is Jeff the Spaceship Captain?]

1808
01:00:09,380 --> 01:00:10,840
Jeff: Let's go find clues.

1809
01:00:11,550 --> 01:00:13,130
Tay: What do you mean?
What kind of nonsense are you making up?

1810
01:00:13,130 --> 01:00:14,060
Phuak: Nothing.

1811
01:00:14,830 --> 01:00:15,400
Jeff: Tay.

1812
01:00:14,900 --> 01:00:16,330
[Tay]

1813
01:00:16,300 --> 01:00:17,280
Jeff: Protect me.

1814
01:00:16,330 --> 01:00:17,950
[Jeff: Protect me]

1815
01:00:18,150 --> 01:00:19,500
Tay: Seriously?

1816
01:00:18,730 --> 01:00:19,800
[Tay: Seriously?]

1817
01:00:20,850 --> 01:00:24,730
[Caught off guard
by the sudden confession]

1818
01:00:25,500 --> 01:00:28,630
[Could Jeff really be
the Spaceship Captain?]

1819
01:00:25,580 --> 01:00:26,640
Jeff: Where are we?

1820
01:00:29,130 --> 01:00:31,390
Phuak: I'm completely confused, no way.

1821
01:00:31,580 --> 01:00:35,050
Phuak: Honestly, I don't even know
if Jeff's telling the truth.

1822
01:00:35,050 --> 01:00:35,650
Tay: Yeah.

1823
01:00:35,750 --> 01:00:38,980
Tay: He suddenly came up to me and said,
“Tay, protect me.”

1824
01:00:40,300 --> 01:00:41,230
Tay: He did this.

1825
01:00:41,630 --> 01:00:42,560
Tay: He did this.

1826
01:00:43,550 --> 01:00:46,150
Tay: What? He told you
he’s the captain, right?

1827
01:00:47,080 --> 01:00:49,030
Tay: No, but the captain
could just say it outright, right?

1828
01:00:49,030 --> 01:00:50,890
Tay: If he wants us to protect him.

1829
01:00:50,930 --> 01:00:52,150
Tay: Oh, but if he... he has no choice.

1830
01:00:52,150 --> 01:00:53,520
Phuak: But what if he's a Human?

1831
01:00:53,520 --> 01:00:56,630
Phuak: He could pretend to be
the captain to get protection.

1832
01:00:56,630 --> 01:01:00,690
Phuak: If he tricks us into going
somewhere remote,
we need to be careful.

1833
01:01:02,230 --> 01:01:04,780
Ink: I'm completely lost. Who's who now?

1834
01:01:04,780 --> 01:01:05,440
Ink: I mean…

1835
01:01:06,700 --> 01:01:10,550
NuNew: But Jeff told me just now
that he's the captain.

1836
01:01:11,080 --> 01:01:12,680
NuNew: He said it seriously.

1837
01:01:13,230 --> 01:01:14,150
NuNew: I don't believe him.

1838
01:01:13,400 --> 01:01:17,600
[Hmm… I don't believe him]

1839
01:01:15,000 --> 01:01:16,130
NuNew: I'd like to reserve my judgment.

1840
01:01:16,130 --> 01:01:18,660
NuNew: Because Jeff tricks me every episode.

1841
01:01:18,700 --> 01:01:20,900
NuNew: So this time, I'm keeping my doubts.

1842
01:01:20,900 --> 01:01:23,630
NuNew: He's basically a 9-tailed,
9-headed fox.

1843
01:01:24,100 --> 01:01:27,750
Phuak: Satur tried to rush over and intercepte.

1844
01:01:27,750 --> 01:01:30,010
Phuak: And he even told us to protect him.

1845
01:01:31,130 --> 01:01:32,730
[Hmm… I don't believe him either]

1846
01:01:31,250 --> 01:01:33,080
Phuak: Satur's playing mind games.

1847
01:01:33,080 --> 01:01:36,490
Phuak: Because if he's a Human
and lies that he's the captain,

1848
01:01:36,550 --> 01:01:38,550
Phuak: he'll get protection.

1849
01:01:39,080 --> 01:01:43,480
Phuak: If we end up somewhere isolated,
he might take me out from the shadows.

1850
01:01:41,430 --> 01:01:44,130
[The trauma left by
being deceived by Jeff]

1851
01:01:44,550 --> 01:01:47,230
Jeff: So, my credibility
is really that low?

1852
01:01:46,180 --> 01:01:50,280
[No one believes me!]

1853
01:01:47,300 --> 01:01:51,160
Jeff: Honestly, since the last episode,
my credibility's been gone.

1854
01:01:51,400 --> 01:01:52,800
Jeff: My image is ruined.

1855
01:01:55,450 --> 01:01:58,040
NuNew: There are about 6 Aliens and 1 captain.

1856
01:01:58,040 --> 01:02:00,040
NuNew: They need to target 2 Humans.

1857
01:02:00,550 --> 01:02:02,610
NuNew: Which means the clue we got is—

1858
01:02:02,930 --> 01:02:07,180
[Mission Clue 3]
[Some Humans have shoe sizes over 40]

1859
01:02:02,950 --> 01:02:06,580
NuNew: Humans have shoe sizes over 40.

1860
01:02:07,430 --> 01:02:11,980
Jeff: Some Humans are single, not married, right?

1861
01:02:10,300 --> 01:02:11,980
[Mission Clue 2]
[Some Humans are “single”]

1862
01:02:12,280 --> 01:02:13,430
Oat: Not married.

1863
01:02:14,500 --> 01:02:15,380
Oat: That rules out Phuak.

1864
01:02:14,730 --> 01:02:16,080
[Let's rule out Phuak first]

1865
01:02:16,200 --> 01:02:17,450
NuNew: Ink isn't a Human.

1866
01:02:17,450 --> 01:02:20,280
NuNew: Because I asked her just now—she's size 39.

1867
01:02:21,980 --> 01:02:25,400
[Phuak & Ink's true identities are “Aliens”]

1868
01:02:26,940 --> 01:02:30,900
[Alien]
[Alien]

1869
01:02:31,430 --> 01:02:34,800
Phuak: We need to find the captain
and then stick with them.

1870
01:02:35,600 --> 01:02:37,630
Phuak: Just protect the captain, that's it.

1871
01:02:35,600 --> 01:02:37,150
[As long as we protect
the captain, we're good]

1872
01:02:37,630 --> 01:02:39,090
Ink: I don't know anymore.

1873
01:02:41,400 --> 01:02:44,480
Ink: I'm suspicious of everyone now.
I wasn't like this before.

1874
01:02:44,480 --> 01:02:46,550
Ink: Now my friends come to talk to me. I...

1875
01:02:46,550 --> 01:02:47,280
Ink: Really?

1876
01:02:47,920 --> 01:02:50,430
Ink: Look into my friend’s eyes.
Are my friend’s eyes sincere?

1877
01:02:50,430 --> 01:02:52,180
Ink: My friend looks into my eyes first—really?

1878
01:02:52,180 --> 01:02:53,040
Ink: Like this.

1879
01:02:53,550 --> 01:02:54,730
Ink: Anyway, I can't trust anyone.

1880
01:02:54,730 --> 01:02:58,590
Ink: That's what I've learned from this show—
you can't trust anyone.

1881
01:02:59,630 --> 01:03:01,500
Ink: This world is more cruel than we think.

1882
01:03:00,550 --> 01:03:02,150
[Reached a state of acceptance]

1883
01:03:02,370 --> 01:03:04,930
Offroad: This is only my third time on this show.

1884
01:03:04,930 --> 01:03:07,830
Offroad: I've figured out
the production team's tricks.

1885
01:03:07,830 --> 01:03:08,800
Offroad: I've grown.

1886
01:03:08,800 --> 01:03:10,450
Offroad: I learn through experience.

1887
01:03:10,450 --> 01:03:13,000
Offroad: Now I know—the person
you can trust the least

1888
01:03:13,000 --> 01:03:15,460
Offroad: is the one closest to you right now.

1889
01:03:15,610 --> 01:03:18,140
Offroad: It's okay, Daou, I'll fight for you.

1890
01:03:18,880 --> 01:03:20,400
TeeTee: Honestly, I'm really nervous.

1891
01:03:20,400 --> 01:03:23,450
TeeTee: The whole day today felt like
we were just playing mini games.

1892
01:03:23,450 --> 01:03:25,650
TeeTee: Because we didn't get any clue.

1893
01:03:27,280 --> 01:03:28,210
Por: Keep going.

1894
01:03:28,750 --> 01:03:30,150
Por: I'm telling myself.

1895
01:03:31,330 --> 01:03:35,300
Commander R: The  Name-Tag Ripping mission
is about to begin. Countdown.

1896
01:03:35,300 --> 01:03:36,350
Commander R: 5.

1897
01:03:36,750 --> 01:03:37,750
Commander R: 4.

1898
01:03:39,200 --> 01:03:40,130
Commander R: 3.

1899
01:03:40,130 --> 01:03:41,530
Phuak: I hate this sound.

1900
01:03:42,250 --> 01:03:43,250
Commander R: 2.

1901
01:03:45,330 --> 01:03:46,190
Commander R: 1.

1902
01:03:47,400 --> 01:03:48,350
Commander R: Game starts.

1903
01:03:47,580 --> 01:03:48,130
[Run]

1904
01:03:51,400 --> 01:03:53,350
Phuak: Let's go, let's search.

1905
01:03:54,130 --> 01:03:56,060
Phuak: Start with this room first.

1906
01:03:56,150 --> 01:03:59,500
Phuak: The most dangerous place
is the safest place.

1907
01:03:59,780 --> 01:04:02,630
Phuak: It's all trash—nothing here.

1908
01:04:05,130 --> 01:04:06,710
[Being careful, staying alert]

1909
01:04:10,230 --> 01:04:11,030
Phuak: Oh my.

1910
01:04:11,800 --> 01:04:13,950
Phuak: Darn it.

1911
01:04:14,400 --> 01:04:17,430
Phuak: It's motion-sensing—
at least give me a warning!

1912
01:04:17,430 --> 01:04:22,350
[This timid Alien even gets
scared by the light bulbs]

1913
01:04:21,250 --> 01:04:23,250
Phuak: My heart just skipped a beat.

1914
01:04:25,780 --> 01:04:30,980
[Alien Ink also starts searching for clues]

1915
01:04:42,280 --> 01:04:45,200
[She finds a clue right away]

1916
01:04:46,960 --> 01:04:49,640
[The true lucky goddess
of Running Man]

1917
01:04:51,640 --> 01:04:55,800
[Human A is a member of
Running Man]

1918
01:04:51,760 --> 01:04:54,980
Ink: Human A is a member of
Running Man.

1919
01:04:57,340 --> 01:04:58,800
Ink: Ah, I got goose bumps.

1920
01:04:59,760 --> 01:05:00,720
Ink: I've got goosebumps.

1921
01:05:00,300 --> 01:05:02,780
[The clue is too vague]

1922
01:05:02,680 --> 01:05:05,480
Ink: There are 7 Running Man
members today, right?

1923
01:05:06,520 --> 01:05:12,520
Ink: 6 people—excluding me,
it leaves Jeff, Tay, Phuak,

1924
01:05:13,360 --> 01:05:15,480
Ink: Oat, and NuNew.

1925
01:05:17,980 --> 01:05:19,380
Ink: That does help a bit.

1926
01:05:20,340 --> 01:05:21,140
Ink: But…

1927
01:05:26,350 --> 01:05:28,660
Ink: Could it be that all the Humans
are actually Running Man members?

1928
01:05:27,460 --> 01:05:32,980
[Are both Humans members of Running Man?]

1929
01:05:28,900 --> 01:05:30,500
Ink: Human B could be one too.

1930
01:05:34,980 --> 01:05:36,060
Por: It's not here, right?

1931
01:05:36,060 --> 01:05:37,820
[The door is locked]

1932
01:05:40,220 --> 01:05:45,380
[Por hasn't gotten any clues yet]

1933
01:05:47,100 --> 01:05:48,230
Por: This is so hard.

1934
01:05:52,500 --> 01:05:57,740
[TeeTee is seriously searching for clues]

1935
01:06:05,780 --> 01:06:10,740
[Running around, he finally finds a clue]

1936
01:06:12,660 --> 01:06:14,940
[Caught red-handed, huh?]

1937
01:06:16,020 --> 01:06:20,340
[You can't trust anyone.
Don't even know who it is—run first]

1938
01:06:22,620 --> 01:06:27,540
[Just got startled by Por,
then got startled again seeing NuNew]

1939
01:06:28,060 --> 01:06:30,780
NuNew: Where are we going?
Wait. Don’t run.

1940
01:06:31,740 --> 01:06:34,380
NuNew: He got a clue.
Where did he find it?

1941
01:06:35,100 --> 01:06:36,860
-NuNew: Tee.
-TeeTee: What?

1942
01:06:38,010 --> 01:06:39,410
NuNew: Did you get a clue?

1943
01:06:39,690 --> 01:06:40,590
TeeTee: Yeah.

1944
01:06:40,730 --> 01:06:42,960
NuNew: I want to know—can you tell me?

1945
01:06:44,010 --> 01:06:44,810
NuNew: Tee.

1946
01:06:44,500 --> 01:06:46,980
[A weak little kitty softly acting cute]

1947
01:06:45,330 --> 01:06:46,640
NuNew: We can share.

1948
01:06:46,970 --> 01:06:47,810
TeeTee: Really?

1949
01:06:47,810 --> 01:06:50,780
NuNew: Whether we share or not depends on you—
it depends on how we play. We can share.

1950
01:06:50,780 --> 01:06:52,380
TeeTee: Then did you find anything, New?

1951
01:06:52,380 --> 01:06:53,210
NuNew: Not yet.

1952
01:06:53,210 --> 01:06:54,790
TeeTee: New, sorry.

1953
01:06:53,460 --> 01:06:55,980
[Refuses instantly]

1954
01:06:55,400 --> 01:06:57,060
TeeTee: Let's talk next time.

1955
01:06:57,540 --> 01:06:59,020
NuNew: You're just running off like that?

1956
01:06:59,020 --> 01:07:00,200
TeeTee: Sorry, bro.

1957
01:07:00,360 --> 01:07:04,400
NuNew: This way's a dead end.
You can't go far—
you'll have to come back out this door anyway.

1958
01:07:04,400 --> 01:07:07,800
NuNew: I was just messing with him.
He's new, it's normal.

1959
01:07:11,660 --> 01:07:14,100
[In front of TeeTee,
even NuNew (the kitty) turns into a beast]

1960
01:07:14,180 --> 01:07:15,780
NuNew: Extremely cautious.

1961
01:07:17,800 --> 01:07:18,980
NuNew: He's extremely cautious.

1962
01:07:18,980 --> 01:07:21,040
NuNew: It's like seeing my past self.

1963
01:07:22,460 --> 01:07:27,740
NuNew: When I first joined Running Man,
I was on full alert too.

1964
01:07:29,540 --> 01:07:33,460
[TeeTee tries his best to run away]

1965
01:07:34,020 --> 01:07:35,280
TeeTee: The clue says—

1966
01:07:37,940 --> 01:07:40,580
[In the English name of the Spaceship Captain,
there are 2 repeated letters]

1967
01:07:41,860 --> 01:07:43,540
[Besides TeeTee, the candidates
for the Spaceship Captain are:]

1968
01:07:43,540 --> 01:07:45,220
[Jeff / NuNew / Offroad]

1969
01:07:46,180 --> 01:07:49,260
[Offroad who fits the Spaceship Captain profile,
is searching for clues]

1970
01:07:46,260 --> 01:07:47,920
Offroad: Whoa.

1971
01:07:48,780 --> 01:07:49,580
Offroad: Bro.

1972
01:07:50,900 --> 01:07:52,160
Offroad: I found this.

1973
01:07:53,980 --> 01:07:55,780
Offroad: The Running Man color.

1974
01:07:56,060 --> 01:07:57,240
Offroad: I'll leave this room first.

1975
01:07:56,220 --> 01:07:59,120
[What clue did Offroad find?]

1976
01:07:59,680 --> 01:08:01,580
Offroad: The Spaceship Captain
was born before the year 2000.

1977
01:08:00,020 --> 01:08:02,740
[The Spaceship Captain was born before 2000]

1978
01:08:02,380 --> 01:08:03,980
Offroad: NuNew's birthday.

1979
01:08:04,140 --> 01:08:06,700
Offroad: Born after 2000.
NuNew was born after 2000.

1980
01:08:06,700 --> 01:08:08,230
Offroad: Who else is there?

1981
01:08:08,460 --> 01:08:09,460
Offroad: Jeff.

1982
01:08:09,460 --> 01:08:11,460
Offroad: Jeff.

1983
01:08:12,410 --> 01:08:15,580
Offroad: Jeff is older than me,
which means he was born before 2000.

1984
01:08:15,580 --> 01:08:18,210
Offroad: I was born in 2000, so he must be
older than me. That leaves just him.

1985
01:08:18,210 --> 01:08:20,569
Offroad: Jeff.
Jeff is the Spaceship Captain.

1986
01:08:20,569 --> 01:08:22,370
Offroad: I need to protect Jeff.

1987
01:08:22,970 --> 01:08:25,229
Offroad: Let's go, I'll find Jeff first.

1988
01:08:28,340 --> 01:08:32,500
[Clues about the Spaceship Captain]
[1. The Spaceship Captain is a singer]

1989
01:08:32,740 --> 01:08:35,580
[All the clues point to…]

1990
01:08:37,779 --> 01:08:40,500
[The true identity of the Spaceship Captain
that the Aliens must protect]

1991
01:08:42,359 --> 01:08:43,720
Jeff: My identity is…

1992
01:08:46,319 --> 01:08:47,720
The Spaceship Captain.

1993
01:08:46,939 --> 01:08:49,859
[Spaceship Captain “Jeff”]

1994
01:08:50,040 --> 01:08:51,540
Jeff: I really am the captain.

1995
01:08:51,540 --> 01:08:53,120
Jeff: You can trust me on this.

1996
01:08:53,120 --> 01:08:55,240
Jeff: I'll take them back safely.

1997
01:09:02,420 --> 01:09:07,580
[Alien] [Alien] [Captain Alien]

1998
01:09:08,819 --> 01:09:11,819
Jeff: I think Phuak
must be an alien.

1999
01:09:08,939 --> 01:09:14,300
[The Spaceship Captain starts looking for Phuak
because he's sure Phuak is an Alien]

2000
01:09:12,420 --> 01:09:13,479
Jeff: Definitely.

2001
01:09:15,620 --> 01:09:20,140
[Doesn't seem convinced;
needs clues to prove himself]

2002
01:09:28,020 --> 01:09:31,620
[He runs into the person
he most wanted to see]

2003
01:09:28,779 --> 01:09:31,580
Phuak: Ugh, of all people,
I run into the monster.

2004
01:09:31,740 --> 01:09:33,500
Jeff: No, no, bro, seriously.

2005
01:09:33,500 --> 01:09:35,060
Phuak: Somewhere remote, huh, Jeff?

2006
01:09:35,060 --> 01:09:36,060
Jeff: Phuak, bro.

2007
01:09:36,670 --> 01:09:39,850
Jeff: I want to stick with you,
because if something happens to me, you can help.

2008
01:09:37,779 --> 01:09:40,779
[A face full of suspicion]

2009
01:09:40,710 --> 01:09:41,979
Phuak: You're not going to
trick me a third time, right?

2010
01:09:41,979 --> 01:09:42,609
Jeff: I'm not lying.

2011
01:09:42,609 --> 01:09:44,630
-Phuak: My heart can only take 2 hits.
-Jeff: This time, this time...

2012
01:09:44,630 --> 01:09:45,790
Jeff: This time it's real, bro.

2013
01:09:45,790 --> 01:09:48,609
Jeff: I got a clue.
I know for sure it's not you.

2014
01:09:49,560 --> 01:09:50,140
Phuak: Not what?

2015
01:09:50,140 --> 01:09:51,100
Jeff: You're definitely not a Human.

2016
01:09:51,100 --> 01:09:51,800
Phuak: Yeah, yeah.

2017
01:09:51,800 --> 01:09:53,979
-Jeff: Right, so...
-Phuak: I don't know if it's true or not.

2018
01:09:52,380 --> 01:09:56,220
[Doesn't trust Jeff,
so he backs off first]

2019
01:09:53,979 --> 01:09:55,600
Phuak: Yeah, yeah, I'll just say yes for now.

2020
01:09:55,600 --> 01:09:57,130
-Phuak: Hello.
-Jeff: Bro.

2021
01:09:57,480 --> 01:09:58,680
Jeff: Think about it.

2022
01:09:58,840 --> 01:10:01,970
Jeff: If I were a Human,
why would I want to stick with you?

2023
01:10:02,600 --> 01:10:04,830
Jeff: I need someone
to go with me, Phuak.

2024
01:10:04,830 --> 01:10:07,310
Phuak: No.
Maybe...Jeff.

2025
01:10:07,310 --> 01:10:10,160
Phuak: Jeff has to admit it—
you hurt my feelings.

2026
01:10:10,290 --> 01:10:12,870
Phuak: You might be a Human
and you're tricking me into protecting you.

2027
01:10:10,300 --> 01:10:13,500
[That actually makes sense]

2028
01:10:13,090 --> 01:10:14,860
Phuak: And then when we were
walking somewhere remote,

2029
01:10:14,860 --> 01:10:16,660
Phuak: you would kill me.

2030
01:10:18,260 --> 01:10:19,940
[Episode 3]
[Monopoly Food Series Game]

2031
01:10:18,900 --> 01:10:19,700
Phuak: Hello.

2032
01:10:20,700 --> 01:10:21,660
[Will you ally with me?]

2033
01:10:21,660 --> 01:10:22,580
[Okay?]

2034
01:10:22,420 --> 01:10:24,700
-Jeff: But we have to pretend we're arguing.
-Phuak: Okay.

2035
01:10:24,700 --> 01:10:25,900
Jeff: When we meet, we should…

2036
01:10:25,900 --> 01:10:27,830
Phuak: Pretend we don’t get along.

2037
01:10:28,340 --> 01:10:29,540
Phuak: Wait, wait, wait.

2038
01:10:28,620 --> 01:10:31,380
[In the end, he got betrayed
and his name tag was torn by Jeff's team]

2039
01:10:32,100 --> 01:10:34,460
[Phuak is out]

2040
01:10:32,100 --> 01:10:34,420
PD: Phuak is out.

2041
01:10:34,860 --> 01:10:36,060
-Phuak: Are you a Ghost?
-Jeff: Yes.

2042
01:10:35,300 --> 01:10:37,580
[Episode 4]
[Ghosts VS Wizards]

2043
01:10:36,060 --> 01:10:37,580
Phuak: Me too.

2044
01:10:37,580 --> 01:10:39,110
Phuak: No, no, I'm a Wizard.

2045
01:10:39,260 --> 01:10:40,500
Jeff: Me too.

2046
01:10:39,540 --> 01:10:41,020
[Blatantly lying with a straight face]

2047
01:10:41,540 --> 01:10:45,420
[And he ended up losing]

2048
01:10:42,540 --> 01:10:45,340
Ink: We won easily.

2049
01:10:45,860 --> 01:10:49,980
Jeff: Wait, Phuak,
you go find clues first.

2050
01:10:49,980 --> 01:10:52,840
Phuak: How about this—
before we split up to search,

2051
01:10:52,870 --> 01:10:53,980
Phuak: what's your shoe size?

2052
01:10:53,980 --> 01:10:55,190
Jeff: What's this?

2053
01:10:54,780 --> 01:10:57,780
[Phuak's clue:
Some Humans have shoe sizes over 40]

2054
01:10:55,190 --> 01:10:56,860
Jeff: I don't know… probably 43.

2055
01:10:56,860 --> 01:10:57,860
-Phuak: What?
-Jeff: 43.

2056
01:10:57,860 --> 01:10:59,860
-Phuak: 43?
-Jeff: Yeah.

2057
01:10:59,380 --> 01:11:01,740
[(Can't trust you)
Alright, you're a Human]

2058
01:11:00,030 --> 01:11:01,590
Phuak: That's a good answer.

2059
01:11:01,590 --> 01:11:03,690
Phuak: Once I get more clues…

2060
01:11:02,340 --> 01:11:03,660
[Tay sneaks in quietly]

2061
01:11:03,690 --> 01:11:05,050
Phuak: Hey, be careful.

2062
01:11:05,920 --> 01:11:07,840
-Jeff: 44—this time 44.
-Phuak: Okay, okay, okay.

2063
01:11:06,380 --> 01:11:08,580
[Thinking “over 40” is good,
so trying hard to prove it]

2064
01:11:08,640 --> 01:11:09,640
Phuak: How about this?

2065
01:11:09,640 --> 01:11:13,480
Phuak: I want to trust you, Jeff,
because I believe you wouldn't hurt me 3 times.

2066
01:11:13,480 --> 01:11:14,240
-Jeff: I won't.
-Phuak: But...

2067
01:11:14,240 --> 01:11:15,620
Tay: Go find clues first.
I don't know—I don't trust him.

2068
01:11:15,620 --> 01:11:16,740
Jeff: Go find clues first, go find clues first.

2069
01:11:16,740 --> 01:11:19,320
-Phuak: Okay, okay.
-Jeff: But if you find anything, come back.

2070
01:11:19,320 --> 01:11:20,900
Phuak: What's the clue? Is it obvious?

2071
01:11:20,900 --> 01:11:22,000
Jeff: Yeah.

2072
01:11:22,000 --> 01:11:26,810
Jeff: The clue says some Humans are single,
unmarried people.

2073
01:11:28,110 --> 01:11:29,690
Jeff: So we can eliminate Phuak right away.

2074
01:11:28,820 --> 01:11:30,860
[So Phuak can be excluded as an Human]

2075
01:11:30,870 --> 01:11:33,010
Tay: Some Humans are single, unmarried people.

2076
01:11:31,860 --> 01:11:33,940
[Unconsciously got clues about the Humans]

2077
01:11:34,260 --> 01:11:35,180
Jeff: Okay?

2078
01:11:34,420 --> 01:11:36,460
[I'm begging you. Seriously]

2079
01:11:35,180 --> 01:11:38,780
Jeff: Please come back to me.
Come back and protect me.

2080
01:11:36,820 --> 01:11:39,060
[Come back to me, come back
and protect me for a bit]

2081
01:11:38,870 --> 01:11:41,500
Jeff: Come back to me, come back
and protect me for a bit.

2082
01:11:41,500 --> 01:11:45,980
[Fully committed;
revealing himself as the Spaceship Captain]

2083
01:11:46,770 --> 01:11:47,750
Jeff: But you go look.

2084
01:11:47,700 --> 01:11:52,100
[Phuak leaves without believing]

2085
01:11:47,890 --> 01:11:50,690
-Phuak: I need clues.
-Jeff: Come back to me, okay?

2086
01:11:51,330 --> 01:11:54,860
Jeff: Tay, if you're an Alien,
if you confirm it, come back to me.

2087
01:11:55,900 --> 01:11:57,900
[Tay leaves first (we'll deal with it later)]

2088
01:11:57,980 --> 01:12:00,860
Jeff: It's over, the plan's useless.
Phuak doesn't believe me.

2089
01:12:00,860 --> 01:12:04,000
Jeff: Because I've hurt him too many times.

2090
01:12:05,980 --> 01:12:07,740
[Alien Ink goes off to search for clues]

2091
01:12:08,140 --> 01:12:11,100
-Ink: To be honest, I did look for...
-Commander R: TeeTee is out.

2092
01:12:09,620 --> 01:12:14,140
[The elimination announcement
suddenly rings out]

2093
01:12:11,500 --> 01:12:13,340
Commander R: TeeTee is out.

2094
01:12:13,340 --> 01:12:14,140
Ink: Ah?

2095
01:12:14,660 --> 01:12:16,700
-Commander R: TeeTee is out.
-Tay: Ah?

2096
01:12:16,700 --> 01:12:18,520
Commander R: TeeTee is out.

2097
01:12:20,300 --> 01:12:23,540
Commander R: Alien TeeTee is out.

2098
01:12:20,660 --> 01:12:24,300
[Alien TeeTee is out]

2099
01:12:23,540 --> 01:12:25,180
NuNew: Just now, TeeTee
got a clue.

2100
01:12:25,180 --> 01:12:28,310
NuNew: But he didn't tell me,
because he didn't trust me.

2101
01:12:28,820 --> 01:12:31,700
[Jeff also hears
TeeTee is out]

2102
01:12:31,940 --> 01:12:34,380
Commander R: Alien TeeTee is out.

2103
01:12:33,060 --> 01:12:36,220
[An Alien out at the beginning of the game]

2104
01:12:36,140 --> 01:12:37,070
Jeff: It's over.

2105
01:12:38,500 --> 01:12:42,180
[Which Human took out TeeTee?]

2106
01:12:42,380 --> 01:12:43,620
[Alien] [Alien] [Alien] [Captain Alien]

2107
01:12:43,620 --> 01:12:47,660
[Alien] [Alien; Out] [Alien] [Captain Alien]

2108
01:12:55,350 --> 01:12:56,660
Oat: Ink, I got a clue.

2109
01:12:56,660 --> 01:12:57,660
Ink: Me too.

2110
01:12:58,350 --> 01:12:59,610
Oat: What's your clue?

2111
01:12:59,630 --> 01:13:01,890
Ink: Nothing, I handed it
to the crew.

2112
01:13:04,510 --> 01:13:06,310
Ink: I'm heading off first, Oat.

2113
01:13:08,460 --> 01:13:11,260
[Ink slips away from Oat]

2114
01:13:12,820 --> 01:13:16,700
[What exactly is Oat's identity?]

2115
01:13:17,610 --> 01:13:18,410
Ink: Oat.

2116
01:13:19,980 --> 01:13:21,040
Ink: Oat is a Human.

2117
01:13:24,080 --> 01:13:25,410
Ink: 100%, 100%.

2118
01:13:28,080 --> 01:13:28,880
Ink: Tay.

2119
01:13:29,520 --> 01:13:30,690
Ink: Tay, Tay, Tay.

2120
01:13:31,040 --> 01:13:31,840
Ink: Tay.

2121
01:13:32,240 --> 01:13:33,040
Ink: Tay.

2122
01:13:33,800 --> 01:13:34,600
Ink: Tay.

2123
01:13:35,840 --> 01:13:38,130
Ink: Oat is definitely a Human.

2124
01:13:39,620 --> 01:13:40,620
Ink: Just now, TeeTee...

2125
01:13:40,620 --> 01:13:43,060
Ink: When I saw TeeTee,
his expression...

2126
01:13:43,060 --> 01:13:46,540
Ink: when Oat walked past,
TeeTee gave that kind of look,

2127
01:13:47,780 --> 01:13:49,240
Ink: Like this, like this.

2128
01:13:51,020 --> 01:13:52,120
Ink: Like this, like this.

2129
01:13:51,580 --> 01:13:53,220
[Wow… Wild Bear is scary]

2130
01:13:53,060 --> 01:13:54,220
Ink: Let me see the clue.

2131
01:13:54,220 --> 01:13:57,080
Ink: My clue is...
Human A is a member of Running Man.

2132
01:13:59,060 --> 01:14:01,940
Ink: The second clue I got is—

2133
01:14:02,780 --> 01:14:03,620
Ink: Human B.

2134
01:14:04,300 --> 01:14:06,620
[Suddenly attacks “Ink”]

2135
01:14:06,860 --> 01:14:07,660
Ink: Human B.

2136
01:14:15,500 --> 01:14:19,380
Ink: Tay, is it you?
Why are you pulling my hair?

2137
01:14:23,220 --> 01:14:25,740
Ink: Why are you pulling my hair?

2138
01:14:25,300 --> 01:14:28,180
[Why tear Ink's name tag?]

2139
01:14:29,860 --> 01:14:33,020
[Human]

2140
01:14:30,030 --> 01:14:30,830
Tay: So?

2141
01:14:30,870 --> 01:14:33,140
Tay: I am the real Human.

2142
01:14:33,140 --> 01:14:36,500
Tay: I sacrificed myself
to infiltrate the Alien group.

2143
01:14:33,780 --> 01:14:37,380
[Tay is a Human]

2144
01:14:37,430 --> 01:14:39,730
Tay: But someone might find out. Why?

2145
01:14:39,730 --> 01:14:43,590
Tay: Because aliens have to act weird,
but I look completely serious.

2146
01:14:50,220 --> 01:14:53,380
[I told you, this is serious]

2147
01:14:58,260 --> 01:15:03,220
[Even the hairstyle causes trouble]

2148
01:15:02,660 --> 01:15:04,320
Tay: My hair got into my mouth.

2149
01:15:05,220 --> 01:15:08,500
[Being an Alien isn't easy]

2150
01:15:09,060 --> 01:15:10,540
Tay: No one noticed.

2151
01:15:11,060 --> 01:15:15,900
[Anyway, I am a Human]

2152
01:15:11,100 --> 01:15:11,940
Tay: Sigh.

2153
01:15:11,940 --> 01:15:13,580
Tay: I'm even starting to
confuse myself, but it's fine.

2154
01:15:13,580 --> 01:15:15,500
Tay: I am the real Human.

2155
01:15:16,500 --> 01:15:18,180
Tay: I sacrificed myself

2156
01:15:18,180 --> 01:15:21,060
Tay: to infiltrate a group
of 7 dangerous Aliens

2157
01:15:21,620 --> 01:15:23,020
Tay: with 1 of my friends.

2158
01:15:26,780 --> 01:15:29,220
[Sorry, I have to take out this Alien first]

2159
01:15:29,820 --> 01:15:31,160
Commander R: Ink is out.

2160
01:15:30,300 --> 01:15:37,340
[Ink is out]

2161
01:15:32,060 --> 01:15:33,390
Commander R: Ink is out.

2162
01:15:34,200 --> 01:15:36,880
Commander R: Alien Ink is out.

2163
01:15:37,340 --> 01:15:38,740
[Alien] [Alien; Out] [Alien] [Captain Alien]

2164
01:15:38,740 --> 01:15:39,700
[Alien] [Alien; Out]
[Alien; Out] [Captain Alien]

2165
01:15:39,700 --> 01:15:42,980
[Alien] [Alien; Out]
[Human] [Alien; Out] [Captain Alien]

2166
01:15:43,340 --> 01:15:45,010
Commander R: Ink is out.

2167
01:15:43,700 --> 01:15:47,700
[The announcement reaches
the Spaceship Captain's ears]

2168
01:15:45,470 --> 01:15:47,210
Commander R: Ink is out.

2169
01:15:47,390 --> 01:15:49,210
Commander R: Ink is out.

2170
01:15:49,600 --> 01:15:51,410
Commander R: Ink is out.

2171
01:15:50,030 --> 01:15:55,230
[The Spaceship Captain
starts getting nervous]

2172
01:15:51,680 --> 01:15:54,860
Commander R: Alien Ink is out.

2173
01:15:55,510 --> 01:15:58,100
-Commander R: Ink is out.
-NuNew: Tay. Tay Tawan.

2174
01:15:58,100 --> 01:15:59,760
-NuNew: Tay Tawan is a Human.
-Commander R: Ink is out.

2175
01:15:59,760 --> 01:16:01,880
-NuNew: Tay, right?
-Offroad: Tay. Tay.

2176
01:16:01,880 --> 01:16:03,210
NuNew: Are you sure?

2177
01:16:03,210 --> 01:16:04,810
NuNew: I don't want to fight.

2178
01:16:06,650 --> 01:16:07,580
Offroad: NuNew.

2179
01:16:08,130 --> 01:16:10,570
Offroad: Tay Tawan ripped off Ink's name tag.

2180
01:16:10,570 --> 01:16:12,980
Offroad: Tay. When I went downstairs,
Tay ripped off Ink's name tag.

2181
01:16:12,980 --> 01:16:15,090
NuNew: I heard Ink
shouting Tay's name just now.

2182
01:16:15,090 --> 01:16:15,890
Offroad: Tay!

2183
01:16:15,460 --> 01:16:19,060
[Because there's a witness,
Human Tay has been exposed]

2184
01:16:24,260 --> 01:16:25,340
Oat: Tay, Tay.

2185
01:16:26,020 --> 01:16:27,180
Oat: Tay, Tay.

2186
01:16:26,740 --> 01:16:28,220
[Oat appears, calling out Tay's name]

2187
01:16:28,260 --> 01:16:30,700
Oat: I think Phuak
and Jeff are over there.

2188
01:16:30,700 --> 01:16:32,830
Oat: Let's split up and circle around.

2189
01:16:35,140 --> 01:16:36,900
Oat: Take one out first, take one out.

2190
01:16:36,900 --> 01:16:39,900
[Oat is controlling the situation]

2191
01:16:40,460 --> 01:16:44,300
[So what exactly is Oat's true identity?]

2192
01:16:45,030 --> 01:16:46,260
Oat: Let's exchange clues.

2193
01:16:46,260 --> 01:16:51,180
[Using a clue exchange to lure TeeTee out]

2194
01:16:47,670 --> 01:16:49,620
Oat: Just for peace of mind,
just for peace of mind.

2195
01:16:49,620 --> 01:16:51,150
Oat: Just for peace of mind.

2196
01:16:52,430 --> 01:16:53,690
TeeTee: Oat, hurry up.

2197
01:16:54,070 --> 01:16:55,170
Oat: Are you going to take me out?

2198
01:16:54,460 --> 01:16:56,980
[Oat looks scary,
different from usual]

2199
01:16:55,670 --> 01:16:57,900
TeeTee: I swear, I swear—
quick, quick, quick.

2200
01:16:57,900 --> 01:16:59,100
[Hehe]

2201
01:16:57,950 --> 01:16:58,950
TeeTee: Hurry up.

2202
01:16:59,940 --> 01:17:01,100
TeeTee: Hurry, Oat.

2203
01:17:00,140 --> 01:17:01,900
[On high alert]

2204
01:17:02,180 --> 01:17:04,660
[Slowly approaching while on high alert]

2205
01:17:02,480 --> 01:17:03,170
Oat: Okay.

2206
01:17:04,940 --> 01:17:05,900
Oat: Okay.

2207
01:17:08,060 --> 01:17:09,300
TeeTee: Ah—Oat!

2208
01:17:09,300 --> 01:17:10,340
[When TeeTee relaxes his guard]

2209
01:17:10,340 --> 01:17:12,900
[When TeeTee relaxes his vigilance,
Wild Bear rushed over immediately]

2210
01:17:10,380 --> 01:17:12,700
TeeTee: Ah, Oat!

2211
01:17:13,780 --> 01:17:15,300
TeeTee: Ah!

2212
01:17:16,540 --> 01:17:20,980
[In an instant, TeeTee's name tag
is ripped off by Wild Bear]

2213
01:17:18,420 --> 01:17:20,340
TeeTee: Ah—ah!

2214
01:17:21,220 --> 01:17:24,580
[TeeTee]

2215
01:17:27,980 --> 01:17:28,780
Oat: Human.

2216
01:17:28,300 --> 01:17:31,980
[Oat: Human]

2217
01:17:32,280 --> 01:17:33,580
Oat: Bro, let me ask you honestly—

2218
01:17:33,580 --> 01:17:35,780
Oat: Do I really look like a Human?

2219
01:17:37,000 --> 01:17:38,620
Oat: The way I look right now—

2220
01:17:38,780 --> 01:17:41,300
Oat: I dressed up as a copyright-safe
version of King Piccolo.

2221
01:17:41,300 --> 01:17:44,060
[How do I look like a Human?]

2222
01:17:44,060 --> 01:17:46,120
Oat: I'm green all over like a pickle.

2223
01:17:48,120 --> 01:17:50,780
Oat: Alright, I'll go invisible—
go invisible.

2224
01:17:52,660 --> 01:17:53,800
Oat: Can you see me?

2225
01:17:53,500 --> 01:17:56,020
[Training to use “invisibility”
to trick TeeTee]

2226
01:17:54,300 --> 01:17:55,300
Oat: Do I blend in?

2227
01:17:55,820 --> 01:17:58,350
Oat: Can you still see me?
Can you still see me?

2228
01:18:01,160 --> 01:18:02,160
Oat: Do I blend in?

2229
01:18:03,720 --> 01:18:05,840
Oat: We're Humans, right?

2230
01:18:06,000 --> 01:18:08,440
Oat: Our role is simple—
we're the hunters.

2231
01:18:06,180 --> 01:18:08,820
[Human Oat with the power of a Wild Bear.]
[The hunting begins.]

2232
01:18:09,200 --> 01:18:10,460
PD: You are a Human.

2233
01:18:10,460 --> 01:18:12,820
PD: But there isn't just one Human.

2234
01:18:12,820 --> 01:18:14,220
Oat: Oh, wow.

2235
01:18:15,200 --> 01:18:16,460
Oat: You want me to read it first?

2236
01:18:16,460 --> 01:18:18,660
PD: It's fine, you can read it together.

2237
01:18:24,060 --> 01:18:24,860
Oat: Brother!

2238
01:18:33,580 --> 01:18:36,180
[Another Human ally: “Tay”]

2239
01:18:36,100 --> 01:18:39,040
PD: Don't let them find out you're Humans.

2240
01:18:39,080 --> 01:18:42,340
Oat: In every game, we have to stay hidden.
We can't be exposed. Okay.

2241
01:18:42,340 --> 01:18:42,820
Oat: Great.

2242
01:18:42,820 --> 01:18:45,080
Tay: We made it through even "Ten-Way Champions,"
so we can definitely win this.

2243
01:18:45,080 --> 01:18:47,220
Oat: Yeah, we're the ultimate
masters of deception.

2244
01:18:47,220 --> 01:18:49,350
Oat: Are you crazy? That's a real stab.

2245
01:18:51,260 --> 01:18:52,940
[Alien] [Alien; Out]
[Human] [Alien; Out] [Captain Alien]

2246
01:18:53,280 --> 01:18:57,060
[Alien] [Alien] [Alien; Out] [Alien]
[Human] [Alien; Out] [Captain Alien] [Human] [Alien]

2247
01:18:58,120 --> 01:19:00,450
Oat: Tay, Tay—there's someone over here.

2248
01:19:00,600 --> 01:19:02,140
-Tay: What?
-Oat: There's someone here.

2249
01:19:02,140 --> 01:19:03,400
-Tay: This way?
-Oat: Tay, go around from that side.

2250
01:19:03,400 --> 01:19:04,600
Oat: I'll go this way.

2251
01:19:08,560 --> 01:19:09,360
Phuak: Hey.

2252
01:19:09,880 --> 01:19:12,000
Phuak: Hey, hey, hey—Oat, Tay.

2253
01:19:12,200 --> 01:19:13,200
Phuak: Oat, Tay.

2254
01:19:13,920 --> 01:19:16,380
-NuNew: Really?
-Phuak: Oat, Tay. Oat, Tay.

2255
01:19:16,960 --> 01:19:18,340
Phuak: Oat, Tay. Oat, Tay.

2256
01:19:18,340 --> 01:19:20,500
[Whispering secretly]

2257
01:19:20,500 --> 01:19:23,660
[They clearly spread out after
spotting the “Humans”]

2258
01:19:23,580 --> 01:19:26,580
Phuak: They're on the same team.
Oat and Tay—not Jeff.

2259
01:19:26,980 --> 01:19:28,860
Phuak: Protect Jeff, protect Jeff.

2260
01:19:28,860 --> 01:19:31,120
Phuak: It seems like it's Oat and Tay now.

2261
01:19:31,180 --> 01:19:33,260
Phuak: Just now they split up to hunt.

2262
01:19:33,260 --> 01:19:35,780
Phuak: We need to find Jeff,
we need to find Jeff.

2263
01:19:35,780 --> 01:19:40,780
[The Aliens have begun
locking onto the Humans]

2264
01:19:39,220 --> 01:19:40,620
Phuak: We need to find Jeff.

2265
01:19:40,620 --> 01:19:43,350
Phuak: Find Jeff.
If we lose Jeff, we're done for.

2266
01:19:48,740 --> 01:19:50,220
-Phuak: Oat and Tay, right?
-Jeff: Regroup.

2267
01:19:50,220 --> 01:19:52,020
-Phuak: Oat and Tay, right?
-Jeff: Oat and Tay. Oat and Tay.

2268
01:19:52,020 --> 01:19:52,660
Jeff: I almost died just now.

2269
01:19:52,660 --> 01:19:54,260
-Jeff: Yes.
-Phuak: Oat and Tay. Oat and Tay.

2270
01:19:54,260 --> 01:19:56,940
-Jeff: I'm the guardian.
-Phuak: Yes, captain.

2271
01:19:55,980 --> 01:19:59,260
[The Aliens finally
start believing the clues]

2272
01:19:57,060 --> 01:19:59,940
-Jeff: Protect me at all costs, okay?
-Phuak: Okay, okay.

2273
01:19:59,940 --> 01:20:01,300
Phuak: Offroad.

2274
01:20:05,810 --> 01:20:07,020
Phuak: What's he holding?

2275
01:20:07,020 --> 01:20:07,900
Phuak: Ah, did he tear it off?

2276
01:20:07,900 --> 01:20:09,900
Phuak: Oh—clue, it's a clue.

2277
01:20:10,090 --> 01:20:11,550
Offroad: The first Human.

2278
01:20:12,050 --> 01:20:15,620
-Offroad: Age—no, weight over...
-Jeff: No need. We already know it's Oat.

2279
01:20:14,940 --> 01:20:17,860
[Am I the only Alien
who knows nothing?]

2280
01:20:18,000 --> 01:20:19,580
Offroad: The Spaceship Captain
was born before 2000.

2281
01:20:19,580 --> 01:20:22,040
Jeff: That's me, that's me—1995, that's me.

2282
01:20:23,100 --> 01:20:25,660
[The Aliens gather to share information]

2283
01:20:25,720 --> 01:20:27,120
Phuak: What should we do?

2284
01:20:27,400 --> 01:20:28,730
Phuak: What's the plan?

2285
01:20:28,920 --> 01:20:30,020
Phuak: What do we do next?

2286
01:20:30,020 --> 01:20:32,480
Offroad: I'll bait them—
let them see it on purpose.

2287
01:20:32,480 --> 01:20:36,080
Offroad: I—I mean by baiting,
I'll show them this clue—they haven't seen it yet.

2288
01:20:36,080 --> 01:20:37,880
Phuak: Be more obvious about it.

2289
01:20:41,740 --> 01:20:45,700
[Offroad goes out to stir things up]

2290
01:20:45,860 --> 01:20:46,660
Phuak: Por.

2291
01:20:48,180 --> 01:20:52,380
Phuak: How about this—for safety's sake,
go look for more clues, just to be sure.

2292
01:20:52,380 --> 01:20:55,300
Phuak: But don't let NuNew
get out of your sight. Watch each other.

2293
01:20:55,300 --> 01:20:56,800
-Por: Yes, bro.
-Phuak: Call NuNew if anything happens.

2294
01:20:56,800 --> 01:20:58,260
-Por: Okay.
-Phuak: Okay.

2295
01:20:58,460 --> 01:21:01,620
[The Aliens use their numbers
to pressure the Humans]

2296
01:21:01,820 --> 01:21:03,820
Phuak: I'm leaving. I'll go find it.

2297
01:21:04,180 --> 01:21:06,380
-Phuak: I'm going to find clues.
-Jeff: Okay, okay.

2298
01:21:06,380 --> 01:21:09,380
[They split up to hunt the Humans]

2299
01:21:09,520 --> 01:21:11,920
Jeff: This is the best strategic position.

2300
01:21:12,420 --> 01:21:15,560
[Aliens have the advantage: 5–2]

2301
01:21:16,420 --> 01:21:23,140
[So the Humans...
will they manage to take down the Aliens?]

2302
01:21:23,220 --> 01:21:30,980
[Who will be the ultimate winner this time?]

2303
01:21:33,260 --> 01:21:34,900
[The Aliens are chasing the hidden Humans]

2304
01:21:38,380 --> 01:21:40,500
Offroad: Phuak, he's gone.

2305
01:21:40,800 --> 01:21:42,820
-Phuak: Huh?
-Offroad: He's not here anymore.

2306
01:21:42,820 --> 01:21:46,300
[The Humans... where did they all go?]

2307
01:21:44,580 --> 01:21:46,180
Phuak: None of them are here?

2308
01:21:53,620 --> 01:21:56,060
[Por runs off without hesitation]

2309
01:22:00,260 --> 01:22:02,640
[Human Oat appears]

2310
01:22:04,820 --> 01:22:08,740
[Runs into Tay face-to-face]

2311
01:22:09,820 --> 01:22:13,460
[The Humans' deception plan
preparing to eliminate all the Aliens]

2312
01:22:15,420 --> 01:22:17,460
[Thrown off balance... what a hard fall]

2313
01:22:20,940 --> 01:22:23,240
[Tay successfully tears off Por's name tag]

2314
01:22:28,420 --> 01:22:31,080
[The moment he hears it,
Spaceship Captain Jeff rushes over]

2315
01:22:34,080 --> 01:22:35,080
Oat: Come on!

2316
01:22:37,000 --> 01:22:39,110
Oat: 2 to 2. 2-2 works too.

2317
01:22:39,700 --> 01:22:43,580
[Come on, Wild Bear of Earth!]

2318
01:22:44,340 --> 01:22:47,060
[The Spaceship Captain is caught
off guard by the Humans' attack]

2319
01:22:44,780 --> 01:22:47,180
Oat: Run! Run!
Run first. We'll talk later.

2320
01:22:48,060 --> 01:22:51,220
[If the Spaceship Captain loses
his name tag, all aliens lose]

2321
01:22:51,340 --> 01:22:54,140
[Falls back first, changing strategy]

2322
01:22:56,740 --> 01:22:57,400
Tay: Sorry.

2323
01:22:58,300 --> 01:23:00,900
[The Aliens are already shaken...]

2324
01:23:00,900 --> 01:23:03,420
-Oat: Por, does it hurt?
-Tay: Are you okay? Are you hurt?

2325
01:23:03,420 --> 01:23:04,220
Por: I'm fine.

2326
01:23:05,900 --> 01:23:09,310
Oat: That leaves Jeff, NuNew,
Phuak and Offroad—4 people.

2327
01:23:10,280 --> 01:23:11,700
PD: Por is out.

2328
01:23:10,380 --> 01:23:14,500
[Alien Por is out]

2329
01:23:12,460 --> 01:23:13,860
PD: Por is out.

2330
01:23:14,720 --> 01:23:17,620
PD: Alien Por is out.

2331
01:23:20,500 --> 01:23:24,420
[Aliens vs. Humans;
The final showdown… no mercy]

2332
01:23:25,660 --> 01:23:27,790
Oat: What's about to happen next is...

2333
01:23:27,940 --> 01:23:30,200
Oat: I might become the one being hunted.

2334
01:23:30,500 --> 01:23:31,960
Oat: Because right now...

2335
01:23:31,960 --> 01:23:33,870
Oat: the member ratio is 4:2.

2336
01:23:35,660 --> 01:23:36,540
Oat: So…

2337
01:23:38,100 --> 01:23:40,360
Oat: we need to protect ourselves first.

2338
01:23:41,540 --> 01:23:44,860
[From now on,
the real game has begun]

2339
01:23:45,220 --> 01:23:49,140
-Jeff: So? Want to go together?
-Offroad: Let's go together and chase them, this way.

2340
01:23:49,140 --> 01:23:53,200
-Jeff: Split up? Go top and bottom, in pairs?
-Phuak: Okay, let's do that.

2341
01:23:54,660 --> 01:23:55,910
Jeff: Is that them?

2342
01:23:56,380 --> 01:23:57,240
Offroad: Is it?

2343
01:23:57,660 --> 01:23:58,670
Offroad: No.

2344
01:23:59,100 --> 01:24:00,760
Jeff: Over there, over there.

2345
01:24:02,220 --> 01:24:04,840
-Offroad: I see them, I see them.
-Jeff: I see them.

2346
01:24:04,840 --> 01:24:06,640
Offroad: Bro, let's go this way.

2347
01:24:08,200 --> 01:24:10,990
Oat: Jeff is coming! Jeff is coming!

2348
01:24:19,110 --> 01:24:20,370
Oat: Jeff is on his way!

2349
01:24:21,030 --> 01:24:22,290
Oat: Jeff is on his way!

2350
01:24:25,980 --> 01:24:32,280
[From hunter to prey]

2351
01:24:32,880 --> 01:24:34,620
Offroad: You need to protect yourself later.

2352
01:24:34,620 --> 01:24:36,880
Offroad: If you are out,
this game is over.

2353
01:24:36,880 --> 01:24:39,910
Offroad: Jeff. I'll go first.

2354
01:24:44,440 --> 01:24:45,700
Tay: Let them only see me.

2355
01:24:45,700 --> 01:24:46,920
Tay: Then you come from behind.

2356
01:24:46,920 --> 01:24:47,580
Tay: I can be the bait.

2357
01:24:47,580 --> 01:24:48,510
Oat: Okay.

2358
01:24:52,040 --> 01:24:53,300
Jeff: Where are they?

2359
01:24:59,400 --> 01:25:00,780
Tay: Oat, you need to stay nearby.

2360
01:25:00,780 --> 01:25:02,350
-Tay: Let them see only me, okay?
-Oat: Okay.

2361
01:25:02,350 --> 01:25:04,210
Oat: When he comes in, you move up.

2362
01:25:15,540 --> 01:25:16,790
Jeff: NuNew, come.

2363
01:25:19,880 --> 01:25:21,340
Jeff: You go take my place.

2364
01:25:22,540 --> 01:25:24,540
NuNew: Jeff, be careful over there.

2365
01:25:35,620 --> 01:25:37,280
Oat: Let's just end this here.

2366
01:25:38,100 --> 01:25:40,000
Offroad: Oat, let's have a final showdown.

2367
01:25:40,000 --> 01:25:44,000
Offroad: Bro, are we just going to
end the game like this? Or should we...

2368
01:25:44,340 --> 01:25:46,390
Offroad: Oh my god, where's Tay?

2369
01:25:47,020 --> 01:25:47,720
Oat: I don't know.

2370
01:25:47,720 --> 01:25:50,250
Offroad: You don't know
How is that possible?

2371
01:25:50,300 --> 01:25:52,700
Offroad: That doesn't sound like you, Oat.

2372
01:26:02,680 --> 01:26:05,140
TeeTee: Ah, Oat is coming!

2373
01:26:05,960 --> 01:26:08,790
Ink: Ah, NuNew!

2374
01:26:10,320 --> 01:26:11,830
Ink: So scary, Phuak!

2375
01:26:11,830 --> 01:26:13,540
-TeeTee: Phuak!
-Ink: Phuak, hurry!

2376
01:26:13,540 --> 01:26:16,020
TeeTee: This is bad, everyone!
On the left!

2377
01:26:16,020 --> 01:26:19,020
TeeTee: Left, left!
They're waiting on the left!

2378
01:26:26,790 --> 01:26:27,720
Oat: Run!

2379
01:26:27,720 --> 01:26:29,030
Offroad: Phuak!

2380
01:26:29,030 --> 01:26:31,370
Oat: Let's go, Tay! Hurry!

2381
01:26:51,240 --> 01:26:52,180
TeeTee: Who is Jeff chasing?

2382
01:26:52,180 --> 01:26:55,110
-Ink: Of course.
Jeff definitely wants to catch Tay.

2383
01:27:04,950 --> 01:27:06,350
Oat: Tay, you go that way!

2384
01:27:06,650 --> 01:27:09,410
Oat: Grab Phuak, let's go together!

2385
01:27:19,020 --> 01:27:21,080
Offroad: Come on, let's go together!

2386
01:27:24,860 --> 01:27:26,780
Phuak: That's enough, that's enough!

2387
01:27:26,780 --> 01:27:28,380
Phuak: You can rip it off now!

2388
01:27:29,020 --> 01:27:30,590
Phuak: It's already torn!

2389
01:27:30,940 --> 01:27:32,740
Phuak: It's already torn, torn!

2390
01:27:33,240 --> 01:27:36,260
Phuak: It's already torn, torn!

2391
01:27:38,520 --> 01:27:39,980
Phuak: It's already torn!

2392
01:27:43,540 --> 01:27:51,440
[Human Oat is out]

2393
01:27:43,540 --> 01:27:45,680
PD: Oat is out.

2394
01:27:45,680 --> 01:27:47,940
PD: Oat is out.

2395
01:27:47,940 --> 01:27:50,630
PD: Human Oat is out.

2396
01:28:01,900 --> 01:28:06,580
[Will the last Human, Tay,
be able to escape?]

2397
01:28:11,040 --> 01:28:13,440
Jeff: Tay is hiding from
his own cameraman.

2398
01:28:14,660 --> 01:28:16,120
Jeff: He's hiding from us.

2399
01:28:18,300 --> 01:28:20,070
NuNew: Tay, are you here?

2400
01:28:20,920 --> 01:28:21,850
NuNew: Not here.

2401
01:28:22,580 --> 01:28:24,240
Phuak: Where did he run off to?

2402
01:28:24,760 --> 01:28:26,090
Phuak: Did you find him?

2403
01:28:26,580 --> 01:28:28,710
-Offroad: I think he's hiding. I didn't find him.
-Phuak: So he's hiding, right?

2404
01:28:28,710 --> 01:28:30,300
-Offroad: I think so.
-Phuak: Okay.

2405
01:28:30,300 --> 01:28:38,800
[Tay... where did he go?]

2406
01:28:39,060 --> 01:28:41,020
[Panting] [Panting]

2407
01:28:41,100 --> 01:28:45,620
[Hiding in the bushes... recharging
before going back to chase Jeff]

2408
01:28:45,940 --> 01:28:47,870
Tay: I'm the only surviving Human.

2409
01:28:47,920 --> 01:28:50,250
Tay: The future of humanity is in my hands.

2410
01:28:50,580 --> 01:28:55,040
[Hiding in the bushes for 10 minutes...]

2411
01:28:55,420 --> 01:28:58,940
Offroad: They say when people
are at their most scared,

2412
01:28:59,340 --> 01:29:01,070
Offroad: adrenaline kicks in.

2413
01:29:01,120 --> 01:29:02,520
Offroad: It just surges.

2414
01:29:04,040 --> 01:29:06,460
Offroad: You get that kind of...
strength from nowhere.

2415
01:29:06,460 --> 01:29:07,790
Offroad: Tay really...

2416
01:29:20,820 --> 01:29:22,880
NuNew: You were hiding in the bushes?

2417
01:29:23,360 --> 01:29:24,710
Tay: I want to go home.

2418
01:29:25,260 --> 01:29:26,860
NuNew: Then just surrender.

2419
01:29:29,140 --> 01:29:30,940
NuNew: Tay, where are you going?

2420
01:29:31,630 --> 01:29:32,990
NuNew: Don't go!

2421
01:29:36,800 --> 01:29:38,060
NuNew: Tay!

2422
01:29:45,830 --> 01:29:46,580
NuNew: Tay!

2423
01:30:03,820 --> 01:30:04,600
NuNew: Tay!

2424
01:30:13,960 --> 01:30:14,820
Offroad: Tay!

2425
01:30:18,600 --> 01:30:20,180
Offroad: Tay, let's talk.

2426
01:30:22,860 --> 01:30:24,380
Offroad: How about an arm wrestle?

2427
01:30:24,380 --> 01:30:26,630
Offroad: Loser gets their name tag torn.

2428
01:30:26,630 --> 01:30:27,890
Offroad: How about it?

2429
01:30:29,640 --> 01:30:31,260
Offroad: Think about it,
our friendship of eating meals together.

2430
01:30:31,260 --> 01:30:33,190
Tay: Right, we've eaten together.

2431
01:30:34,320 --> 01:30:35,740
Offroad: Just surrender and end the game.

2432
01:30:35,740 --> 01:30:37,470
Offroad: I know you want to win.

2433
01:30:38,100 --> 01:30:40,140
Offroad: Oh man!

2434
01:30:42,940 --> 01:30:44,740
Tay: Oh my god, why me?

2435
01:31:06,940 --> 01:31:07,900
Offroad: Tay!

2436
01:31:08,420 --> 01:31:10,240
Tay: Don't come at me,
I can't beat you.

2437
01:31:10,240 --> 01:31:11,540
Offroad: You can.

2438
01:31:40,320 --> 01:31:42,990
Tay: I don't want to go home yet.

2439
01:31:43,040 --> 01:31:44,140
Tay: Spare me.

2440
01:31:46,620 --> 01:31:48,020
Jeff: Offroad, go for it!

2441
01:31:53,720 --> 01:31:54,860
Offroad: Ah, don't bite me!

2442
01:31:54,860 --> 01:31:56,860
Offroad: Don't bite me, don't bite!

2443
01:31:58,980 --> 01:32:01,200
[Not that easy to take down]

2444
01:32:01,660 --> 01:32:05,660
[But the Alien Offroad is too fast]

2445
01:32:24,320 --> 01:32:25,920
Jeff: Tay, you did your best.

2446
01:32:36,660 --> 01:32:37,460
Jeff: Are you hurt?

2447
01:32:37,460 --> 01:32:39,590
Offroad: You're not hurt, right?
I tried my best to protect you.

2448
01:32:39,590 --> 01:32:41,380
PD: Tay is out.

2449
01:32:40,300 --> 01:32:47,380
[Human Tay is out]

2450
01:32:42,080 --> 01:32:44,500
PD: Human Tay is out.

2451
01:32:44,680 --> 01:32:47,220
PD: The Name-Tag Ripping Mission is over.

2452
01:32:51,120 --> 01:32:53,260
Ink: Yay!

2453
01:32:56,520 --> 01:32:59,340
PD: So for today's Name-Tag Ripping Mission,

2454
01:32:59,340 --> 01:33:01,020
